note right of FormalCore
This is the part to trust first.
It carries the strongest current evidence.
end note

note right of StateOpen
This box is the anti-overclaim guardrail.
Team programmers should add code here as explicit theorem owners,
not as extra prose on existing packages.
end note

note right of CoreSpineContraction
CoreSpine is a bridge layer:
it exposes one typed ternary carrier,
one agreement ultrametric,
one contraction-certificate interface,
and the bounded CRT/J scalar channel.
It does not discharge concrete descent
or prove biology/chemistry/physics closure.
end note

note left of BridgeLayers
Important correction:
some recovery structure is already theorem-bearing here.
The open gap is stronger physical recovery,
not total absence of bridge theorems.
end note

note right of EmpiricalLane
Useful for calibration and interpretation contracts.
Not evidence of theorem closure by itself.
Current chi2 audit reports a carrier mismatch;
current B4 shell comparison is standaloneOnly.
end note

note right of MusicAttractor
Music target is precise but bounded:
Z12 carrier, chromatic metric,
K_music projection, L_music descent.
No perception, uniqueness, Monster-prime,
or physics-closure claim is made.
end note

note left of DNALane
Important scope split:
the DNA lane is now genuinely localized in Agda,
but it is not itself a physics-unification theorem lane.
The brain lane now has theorem-thin local owner/summary/extraction/invariant/invariant-depth surfaces,
while its richer archive-backed brain themes are kept separate in explicit blocker boxes,
and the crossover lane now has partial local owner/compatibility/law/consumer/connector/depth/semantic/composition/payload surfaces,
with its own explicit blocker box kept separate from the lane object,
but neither is local theorem closure here.
end note

note right of ConnectorChain
This is the clearest currently local
brain -> DNA -> chemistry -> physics path.
It is now explicit and consumed through
theme transport, bounded representation semantics,
bounded representation transport laws,
bounded representation semantic-depth,
bounded representation semantic-laws,
bounded representation-consumer semantics/laws,
bounded representation-integrated semantics,
codec/chemistry consumption,
connector semantic-depth,
theme-to-chemistry/channel transport,
theme semantic-transport laws,
theme end-to-end semantic-depth,
theme-consumer semantics/laws,
theme-integrated semantics,
connector end-to-end semantic-laws,
connector-consumer semantics/laws,
connector-integrated consumer semantics,
and a bounded physics-facing handoff,
but it remains theorem-thin.
end note

note bottom of BlockerContinuum
This is the live non-claim boundary.
The repo is not entitled to cross it yet.
Several lanes are now advanced or explicitly blocker-bound,
not "missing from zero."
end note

